            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThese%20sobering%20words%20were%20delivered%20to%20a%20false%20prophet%20named%20Hananiah%2C%20who%20had%20prophesied%20that%20the%20Jewish%20people%20would%20be%20restored%20from%20Babylon%20within%20two%20years.%20This%20prophecy%20contradicted%20Jeremiah's%20clear%20teaching%20that%20they%20would%20be%20captives%20in%20Babylon%20for%20seventy%20years%2C%20not%20two.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20has%20always%20had%20his%20prophets%20who%20look%20right%20and%20sound%20right.%20They%20are%20like%20Hymenaeus%20and%20Alexander%2C%20who%20shipwrecked%20their%20own%20faith%20by%20teaching%20that%20the%20resurrection%20was%20past%20(1%20Timothy%201%3A19-20).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFalse%20doctrine%20works%20its%20way%20into%20churches%20as%20well%20as%20into%20individuals.%20It%20misleads%20and%20steers%20away%20from%20faith%20and%20a%20good%20conscience.%20All%20true%20teaching%20will%20produce%20%22love%20that%20comes%20from%20a%20pure%20heart%2C%20a%20clear%20conscience%2C%20and%20sincere%20faith%22%20(v.%205).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJudge%20all%20teaching.%20The%20teaching%20may%20look%20good%20and%20sound%20right%2C%20but%20does%20it%20lead%20to%20godly%20actions%3F%20Does%20it%20lead%20people%20away%20from%20%22talking%20foolishness%22%20(v.%206)%20and%20cause%20them%20to%20focus%20on%20saving%20sinners%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EKeep%20your%20doctrinal%20ship%20steered%20down%20the%20center%20of%20the%20channel.%20Beware%20of%20the%20shorelines%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20appealing.%20The%20rocks%20of%20destruction%20lurk%20just%20beneath%20the%20surface!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
